Warm Up Activity

Which one doesn’t belong?






Enter your answer here:

Compare your answers:

  • Graph A is the only graph that has a positive vertical intercept and a positive horizontal intercept. It is the only one that has a constant, negative rate of change.
  • Graph B is the only graph that is not a continuous curve and has multiple pieces. It is the only one that shows both points and lines.
  • Graph C is the only graph that has a constant \(y\)-value.
  • Graph D is the only graph whose \(y\)-value increases and decreases multiple times. It is the only graph that is not a simple line or curve and that has wave-like features.
